{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860301358,"sessionID":"ses_2867adb84ffeLVz7bjGSwZoHaq","part":{"id":"prt_d7985b9ae0012cPxw8LaVzFeMt","messageID":"msg_d79858128001ij44NID0Rb3WFR","sessionID":"ses_2867adb84ffeLVz7bjGSwZoHaq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-5540ab7cf32242b7a3dfb1b193a024fb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-015/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-015/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015 ŌĆö PicoD ÕæĮõ╗żµē¦ĶĪī API Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-015 ŌĆö PicoD ÕæĮõ╗żµē¦ĶĪī API |\n8: | Module | `pkg/picod` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: [TO BE FILLED: Design overview and description]\n14: \n15: ## Architecture\n16: \n17: [TO BE FILLED: Architecture diagram and description]\n18: \n19: ## Data Structures\n20: \n21: [TO BE FILLED: Key data structures]\n22: \n23: ## API Contracts\n24: \n25: [TO BE FILLED: API specifications]\n26: \n27: ## Error Handling\n28: \n29: [TO BE FILLED: Error handling strategy]\n30: \n31: ## Testing Strategy\n32: \n33: [TO BE FILLED: Testing approach]\n34: \n35: ## File Structure\n36: \n37: [TO BE FILLED: File organization]\n38: \n39: ## Dependencies\n40: \n41: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n42: |---------|---------|---------|\n43: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n44: \n45: ## Implementation Notes\n46: \n47: [TO BE FILLED: Implementation details and patterns]\n48: \n49: ## References\n50: \n51: - [TO BE FILLED: Related documents]\n\n(End of file - total 51 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015 ŌĆö PicoD ÕæĮõ╗żµē¦ĶĪī API Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-015 ŌĆö PicoD ÕæĮõ╗żµē¦ĶĪī API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Design overview and description]\n\n## Architecture\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Architecture diagram and description]\n\n## Data Structures\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-015/design.md","time":{"start":1775860301338,"end":1775860301356}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860301361,"sessionID":"ses_2867adb84ffeLVz7bjGSwZoHaq","part":{"id":"prt_d7985bdfd001P3ReC1subBod07","messageID":"msg_d79858128001ij44NID0Rb3WFR","sessionID":"ses_2867adb84ffeLVz7bjGSwZoHaq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-20bbdedde3a742eb9159be6ed566ade1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md","limit":200},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-009 ŌĆö Router HTTP ÕÅŹÕÉæõ╗ŻńÉåµĀĖÕ┐ā\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/router`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define the HTTP reverse proxy core for the AgentCube Router component. This provides session-aware routing that resolves session IDs from request headers, creates sandboxes via Workload Manager, forwards HTTP requests to sandbox pod endpoints using `httputil.ReverseProxy`, generates RS256-signed JWT tokens, updates session activity timestamps, and limits concurrent requests via semaphore middleware.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Server type definition\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define `Server` as an HTTP server with Gin engine for reverse proxy routing.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Server struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `Server` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `config *Config` for server configuration\n26:   - `engine *gin.Engine` for Gin HTTP framework\n27:   - `httpServer *http.Server` for underlying HTTP server\n28:   - `sessionManager SessionManager` for session resolution\n29:   - `store Store` for session state persistence\n30:   - `jwtManager JWTManager` for JWT token generation\n31:   - `transport *http.Transport` for HTTP transport sharing\n32:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: Config struct definition\n35: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/config.go`\n36: - **WHEN** reading the `Config` struct\n37: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n38:   - `Port int` for listening port (default 8080)\n39:   - `EnableTLS bool` for TLS enablement\n40:   - `TLSCert string` for TLS certificate file path\n41:   - `TLSKey string` for TLS private key file path\n42:   - `MaxConcurrentRequests int` for concurrency limit\n43:   - `Debug bool` for debug mode\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: NewServer constructor\n46: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n47: - **WHEN** calling `NewServer(config *Config, sessionManager SessionManager, store Store, jwtManager JWTManager, logger Logger)`\n48: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*Server` with:\n49:   - `engine` initialized with `gin.New()`\n50:   - `gin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)` if `config.Debug == false`\n51:   - `gin.SetMode(gin.DebugMode)` if `config.Debug == true`\n52:   - `transport` initialized with shared HTTP transport\n53:   - `httpServer` initialized with h2c configuration\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: DefaultConfig\n56: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/config.go`\n57: - **WHEN** calling `DefaultConfig()`\n58: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*Config` with:\n59:   - `Port` = `8080`\n60:   - `EnableTLS` = `false`\n61:   - `MaxConcurrentRequests` = `1000`\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ### Requirement: Server lifecycle\n66: \n67: The system SHALL provide Start/Stop lifecycle methods with graceful shutdown.\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Start without TLS\n70: - **GIVEN** a `Server` with `config.EnableTLS == false`\n71: - **WHEN** calling `server.Start(ctx)`\n72: - **THEN** `httpServer.ListenAndServe()` SHALL be called\n73: - AND h2c server SHALL handle HTTP/2 without TLS\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Start with TLS\n76: - **GIVEN** a `Server` with `config.EnableTLS == true`\n77: - **WHEN** calling `server.Start(ctx)`\n78: - **THEN** `httpServer.ListenAndServeTLS(config.TLSCert, config.TLSKey)` SHALL be called\n79: - AND error SHALL be returned if cert/key files are missing\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Graceful shutdown\n82: - **GIVEN** a running `Server`\n83: - **WHEN** context is cancelled\n84: - **THEN** `httpServer.Shutdown(shutdownCtx)` SHALL be called\n85: - AND shutdown deadline SHALL be `10s`\n86: - AND server SHALL stop accepting new connections\n87: - AND existing connections SHALL complete\n88: \n89: #### Scenario: Server timeouts\n90: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n91: - **WHEN** initializing `httpServer`\n92: - **THEN** timeouts SHALL be configured:\n93:   - `ReadTimeout` = `30s`\n94:   - `IdleTimeout` = `90s`\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: ### Requirement: Route registration\n99: \n100: The system SHALL register routes for health endpoints and invocation paths.\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: Health routes\n103: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n104: - **WHEN** registering routes\n105: - **THEN** `/health/live` SHALL be registered with `handleHealthLive`\n106: - AND `/health/ready` SHALL be registered with `handleHealthReady`\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Invocation routes\n109: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n110: - **WHEN** registering routes\n111: - **THEN** `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` SHALL be registered\n112: - AND `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` SHALL be registered\n113: - AND both `GET` and `POST` methods SHALL be supported\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Middleware chain\n116: - **GIVEN** route registration\n117: - **WHEN** applying middleware\n118: - **THEN** `concurrencyLimitMiddleware` SHALL be applied globally\n119: - AND `loggingMiddleware` SHALL be applied for request logging\n120: - AND `recoveryMiddleware` SHALL be applied for panic recovery\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ### Requirement: SessionManager interface\n125: \n126: The system SHALL define `SessionManager` interface for session resolution and sandbox creation.\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: SessionManager interface definition\n129: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n130: - **WHEN** reading the `SessionManager` interface\n131: - **THEN** interface SHALL include:\n132:   - `GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID, namespace, name, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n133: \n134: #### Scenario: manager struct definition\n135: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n136: - **WHEN** reading the `manager` struct\n137: - **THEN** struct SHALL contain:\n138:   - `storeClient Store` for session lookup\n139:   - `workloadMgrAddr string` for Workload Manager URL\n140:   - `httpClient *http.Client` for sandbox creation requests\n141:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: NewSessionManager constructor\n144: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n145: - **WHEN** calling `NewSessionManager(store Store, logger Logger)`\n146: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*manager` with:\n147:   - `workloadMgrAddr` from `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable\n148:   - startup SHALL fail if `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is not set\n149:   - `httpClient` with `Timeout=2m`, `MaxIdleConnsPerHost=100`\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: HTTP client configuration\n152: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n153: - **WHEN** initializing `httpClient`\n154: - **THEN** HTTP2 SHALL be configured with:\n155:   - `ReadIdleTimeout` = `30s`\n156:   - `PingTimeout` = `15s`\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: ### Requirement: Session resolution\n161: \n162: The system SHALL resolve sessions by ID and create new sandboxes when missing.\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: GetSandboxBySession with existing session\n165: - **GIVEN** a session ID that exists in store\n166: - **WHEN** calling `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)`\n167: - **THEN** `store.GetSession(ctx, sessionID)` SHALL be called\n168: - AND `*SandboxInfo` SHALL be returned if found\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: GetSandboxBySession creates new sandbox\n171: - **GIVEN** a session ID that does NOT exist in store\n172: - **WHEN** calling `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)`\n173: - **THEN** `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)` SHALL be called\n174: - AND POST request SHALL be sent to Workload Manager\n175: \n176: #### Scenario: createSandbox POST request\n177: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n178: - **WHEN** calling `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)`\n179: - **THEN** POST SHALL be sent to:\n180:   - `/v1/agent-runtime` for `AgentRuntimeKind`\n181:   - `/v1/code-interpreter` for `CodeInterpreterKind`\n182: - AND request body SHALL be `CreateSandboxRequest`\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: createSandbox with K8s SA token\n185: - **GIVEN** in-cluster deployment\n186: - **WHEN** sending POST to Workload Manager\n187: - **THEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` SHALL be read\n188: - AND token SHALL be set as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: createSandbox namespace\n191: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n192: - **WHEN** creating sandbox\n193: - **THEN** `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` environment variable SHALL be read for target namespace\n194: - AND default namespace SHALL be `\"default\"` if not set\n195: \n196: ---\n197: \n198: ### Requirement: Reverse proxy implementation\n199: \n200: The system SHALL implement reverse proxy with custom Director and error handling.\n\n(Showing lines 1-200 of 927. Use offset=201 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-009 ŌĆö Router HTTP ÕÅŹÕÉæõ╗ŻńÉåµĀĖÕ┐ā\n\n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the HTTP reverse proxy core for the AgentCube Router component. This provides session-aware routing that resolves session IDs from request headers, creates sandboxes via Workload Manager, forwards HTTP requests to sandbox pod endpoints using `httputil.ReverseProxy`, generates RS256-signed JWT tokens, updates session activity timestamps, and limits concurrent requests via semaphore middleware.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Server type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `Server` as an HTTP server with Gin engine for reverse proxy routing.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775860301343,"end":1775860301359}}}}
